description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band 4 Cancer Rehabilitation Support Worker - Care Coordination&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Part Time: 22.5 hours per week&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This exciting post has been developed with the cancer rehabilitation team at the Royal Berkshire Hospital to support people to live well with and beyond cancer.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will work under the supervision of registered practitioners providing patients and carers affected by cancer with general information and support about cancer related issues and cancer services. The role has a focus on supporting self-management and behaviour change to live well and thrive.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;By supporting independence and self-management, the role will enable patients to navigate the health and social care system and make choices that are best for their cancer and their lifestyle.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will demonstrate a partnership approach in order to empower the patient and carers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post also provides administrative duties and support to the cancer rehabilitation team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will have excellent communication skills, be able to coordinate, organise and work well within a small team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Training will be provided by both Macmillan Cancer Support and the Royal Berkshire Hospital and the working environment is friendly and supportive.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful post holder will provide the cancer rehabilitation team with support and will liaise across a wider multi-disciplinary team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Lisa Moyles (CNS Team Leader) on 0118 322 7511 or lisa.moyles@royalberkshire.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
